radiographic_examinations.findings: There is a 3-mm pulmonary nodule in the left lung base. The liver demonstrates homogeneous enhancement without suspicious focal lesions. The gallbladder is mildly distended. The appendix is fluid filled and dilated to 15 mm with hyperemic wall. Slightly limited evaluation for fat stranding with trace amount of fluid within the abdomen. No evidence of perforation or periappendiceal fluid collection or abscess formation. Small and large bowel loops are normal in caliber. Post-surgical changes related to recent C-section are noted. Small amount of free fluid is seen within the pelvis. Right ovarian corpus cyst is visualized. No suspicious lytic or sclerotic bony lesion is seen.
